		<div class="col-md-7 col-12 pl-0">
		    
			<p class="ml-3 mt-1">A married pair hailing from the surface, Cordelia and Theodore have made themselves at home in the Neath. </p>
			<p class="ml-3">While they do speak ever so fondly of each other, you'd be hard pressed to see them together. They frequent very different areas with very different types of people, often expressing a friendly distaste in the other's choice in company.</p>
			<p class="ml-3">Cordelia is an upstanding lady, often found at a variety of high society revels and art galleries. Although, on paper, her profession is that of a tailor, you'll more likely know her from planning and organizing many events like these.</p>
			<p class="ml-3">Theodore is much more excitable and reckless than his counterpart, frequenting the docks and Watchmaker's hill. He's often seen challenging others or hunting strange creatures, just for the thrill of the chase. The rewards are a bonus.</p>
			<p class="ml-3">It truly is a pity that the pair don't spend time together in public, they'd be such a striking couple. In fact, if you happen to find yourself in often company of both Mr and Mrs Pembroke, you'll find that they are quite physically similar, despite their other differences. Cordelia will sometimes mention that they've been mistaken for siblings or even the same person; what a simple misunderstanding, indeed... Unless?</p>
			<hr class="ml-3">
			<p class="ml-3">Theodore and Cordelia are, in reality, one and the same. These are simply facets of Pembroke as a whole - personas that let her explore very distinct aspects of society and herself. Part high society, part adrenaline junkie, just one genderfluid mess. Overall somewhat chaotic and a menace, not afraid to cause a scene to have some fun.</p>
			
		</div>
				
